Indeed, it was at Dave&#39;s suggestion to try this method that I became of fan of manual radio sweep (though I think it had been around for ages prior to that, I&#39;d never heard of it.) I find Dave&#39;s experiments to be endlessly fascinating.  Surely seems he got a double-dose, or more, of innate smartness and creativity.  ;-)  

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Misty Dawn &lt;bulletbabea@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Yep ever since Frank Sumption and Retro Dave mentioned trying it and I did, I find it fascinating and very useful as a tool. I waited a long time for them to &quot;work together&quot; as spirit said they would and that conversation is here in the archives. Works great and allows for adjustments easily.
&gt; 
&gt; Thanks again to those guys for chit chatting here that day! I agree everyone should try it! No box needed for sweep tuning method.
